<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF9FEF52FF42F8DFFDD6FE69" lastPageId="57" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9FEF5CFF42F8DFFD2EF874" blockId="55.[151,1436,1825,1997]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9FEF5CFF42F8DFFEE7F83C" bold="true" box="[199,338,1898,1924]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Comments:</emphasis>
The collected specimens have an interesting colouration pattern, when alive they are greyish with some greenish areas or spots, and with ventral edge of abdomen light brown. They camouflage on mosses and lichens, where they can be found and collected.
</paragraph>
<caption id="09BB5CE3FF90EF53FF12F8F0FC6DF855" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550135" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6550135" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550135/files/figure.png" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" startId="56.[151,250,1861,1885]" targetBox="[239,1353,184,1836]" targetPageId="56">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF90EF53FF12F8F0FC6DF855" blockId="56.[151,1437,1861,2030]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF90EF53FF12F8F0FE94F8E5" bold="true" box="[151,289,1861,1885]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">FIGURE 30.</emphasis>
Calling songs of the species of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF90EF53FDEDF8F0FCBAF8E5" authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[616,783,1861,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pseudophyllinae">Pseudophyllinae</taxonomicName>
from the ParNa Iguaçu. A–C: 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF90EF53FBCFF8F0FAEFF8E5" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[1098,1370,1861,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Meroncidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavolimbatus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF90EF53FBCFF8F0FAEFF8E5" box="[1098,1370,1861,1885]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Meroncidius flavolimbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; D–F: 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF90EF53FF12F8DCFEDEF839" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,363,1897,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Dasyscelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="normalis">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF90EF53FF12F8DCFEDEF839" box="[151,363,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Dasyscelus normalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; G–I: 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF90EF53FE35F8DCFD54F839" box="[432,737,1897,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyteleutias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavolimbatus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF90EF53FE35F8DCFD54F839" box="[432,737,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Brachyteleutias flavolimbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A: sonogram of one echeme (the “noise” before the echeme corresponds to drumming behaviour); B: sonogram of one echeme; C: spectrogram of one syllable; D: sonogram of three echemes; E: sonogram of one echeme; F: sonogram of two syllables, (note the change of dominant frequency along time); G: sonogram of one echeme; H and I: sonogram and spectrogram of two syllables, respectively.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF91EF52FF42FF23FDFEFEF9" blockId="57.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF91EF52FF42FF23FEEEFF08" bold="true" box="[199,347,150,176]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFF91EF52FEE9FF22FE43FF09" box="[364,502,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1861,1885]" captionTargetBox="[239,1353,184,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-29@56.[231,1357,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 30. Calling songs of the species of Pseudophyllinae from the ParNa Iguaçu. A–C: Meroncidius flavolimbatus; D–F: Dasyscelus normalis; G–I: Brachyteleutias flavolimbatus. A: sonogram of one echeme (the “noise” before the echeme corresponds to drumming behaviour); B: sonogram of one echeme; C: spectrogram of one syllable; D: sonogram of three echemes; E: sonogram of one echeme; F: sonogram of two syllables, (note the change of dominant frequency along time); G: sonogram of one echeme; H and I: sonogram and spectrogram of two syllables, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550135" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550135/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 30D–F</figureCitation>
): Males produce echemes with small duration and quite constant amplitude. Each echeme is composed by 22 to 28 syllables with a moderate increasing of intensity during the sound production. A remarkable characteristic of the song of the species is that the dominant frequency changes along the stridulation: the dominant frequency is smaller at the beginning and at the end of the syllable than in the middle of the syllable, when the highest frequency is reached.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF91EF52FF42FEFEFDDCFEDD" blockId="57.[151,1437,150,465]" box="[199,617,331,357]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF91EF52FF42FEFEFE1EFEDD" box="[199,427,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Dominant frequency</emphasis>
: 19.6 ± 2.2 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF91EF52FF42FEDAFE45FE31" blockId="57.[151,1437,150,465]" box="[199,496,367,393]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF91EF52FF42FEDAFEF5FE31" box="[199,320,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Bandwidth</emphasis>
: 6.9 ± 0.8 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF91EF52FF42FE26FD87FE15" blockId="57.[151,1437,150,465]" box="[199,562,403,429]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF91EF52FF42FE26FE9BFE14" box="[199,302,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Duration</emphasis>
: Syllable: 0.3 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFF91EF52FE6DFE26FD98FE15" box="[488,557,403,429]" degrees="0.02" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" precision="555" value="-0.02">0.02 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF91EF52FF42FE02FDD6FE69" blockId="57.[151,1437,150,465]" box="[199,611,439,465]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF91EF52FF42FE02FEEAFE69" box="[199,351,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Mute interval</emphasis>
: Syllable: 14.2 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFF91EF52FDA2FE02FDEBFE69" box="[551,606,439,465]" degrees="2.2" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" precision="5555" value="-2.2">2.2 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
